<p>
  {gettext(
    "P2P Games lets you play retro arcade games directly with another user. Games run in real-time over WebRTC DataChannel — no server relay, minimal latency. 15 base games with 20 additional mode variants across action, sports, racing, and co-op genres."
  )}
</p>
<.help_h4 icon={:icon_send}>{gettext("Starting a Game")}</.help_h4>
<pre>{gettext("/game <nickname>")}</pre>
<p>
  {gettext(
    "This creates a game session and sends an invite via PM. The target user clicks the link to join the game lobby."
  )}
</p>
<.help_h4 icon={:icon_community}>{gettext("Game Lobby")}</.help_h4>
<p>
  {gettext("The lobby is where both players meet before starting a game. You can:")}
</p>
<ul>
  <li>{gettext("Chat with your opponent")}</li>
  <li>{gettext("Browse and select from 35 available games across 15 families")}</li>
  <li>{gettext("Wait for your opponent to accept or decline")}</li>
</ul>
<p>
  {gettext("Game selection requires")} <strong>{gettext("bilateral consent")}</strong>
  {gettext("— one player picks a game, the other must accept before it starts.")}
</p>
<.help_h4 icon={:icon_game_generic}>{gettext("Available Games")}</.help_h4>
<ul>
  <li>
